(807, 20, 'Anatomy Guide (Pocket Book)', 'https://lh3.ggpht.com/azpyZ9zcOtdn1UzgB3MA9grc0PJcSYHa2j0pOoiX-kTUNE03DMr-IwOJlI-jFn6wIQ=w300', '', 'https://lh6.ggpht.com/YTiusbMYhfMjGG8WjvGYMUr3nHW4XNZpN8yyezXTzhmuUssyQsu2qTQL2PQmgBPoCVI=h310,https://lh4.ggpht.com/APpN_GvDCb-io2AZBLFzqYqwCgyW5n-Q5iXeqoYmbNBfCy2d8BOioEzDsBt5cr6Icw=h310,https://lh3.ggpht.com/RZWJGwcrM5xBiH17A8TxN-xD4IlXGGvud4fhIsFwip5GJVIHUDmnyC8JMc0x5N9jUhON=h310,https://lh5.ggpht.com/NLcxfIlMzBrYHYIPJsjy8M2pLkZk18rCZygXUhHQP0qM7EyvitZQ8u3MdLeJdQSpeg=h310,https://lh6.ggpht.com/gScVJDJgz_aZ344viyVScTWXXrpe1B3Y1IYTJMnW1v4_WWfNMBuUWqUIe-CKhdzb-g=h310', 'Anatomy is subdivided into gross anatomy and microscopic anatomy. Gross anatomy (also called topographical anatomy, regional anatomy, or anthropotomy) is the study of anatomical structures that can be seen by the naked eye. Microscopic anatomy is the study of minute anatomical structures assisted with microscopes, which includes histology (the study of the organization of tissues), and cytology (the study of cells). Anatomy, human physiology (the study of function), and biochemistry (the study of the chemistry of living structures) are complementary basic medical sciences that are generally together (or in tandem) to students studying medical sciences. Generally, physicians, dentists, physiotherapists, nurses, paramedics, radiographers, and students of certain biological sciences, learn gross anatomy and microscopic anatomy from anatomical models, skeletons, textbooks, diagrams, photographs, lectures, and tutorials. The study of microscopic anatomy (or histology) can be aided by practical experience examining histological preparations (or slides) under a microscope; and in addition, medical and dental students generally also learn anatomy with practical experience of dissection and inspection of cadavers (dead human bodies). A thorough working knowledge of anatomy is required for all medical doctors, especially surgeons, and doctors working in some diagnostic specialities, such as histopathology and radiology.\nHuman anatomy, physiology, and biochemistry are basic medical sciences, which are generally taught to medical students in their first year at medical school. Human anatomy can be taught regionally or systemically; that is, respectively, studying anatomy by bodily regions such as the head and chest, or studying by specific systems, such as the nervous or respiratory systems. The major anatomy textbook, Gray s Anatomy, has recently been reorganized from a systems format to a regional format, in line with modern teaching.\n\n\nHere we shall cover some part of human anatomy, which can be used by the user as a quick reference whenever he/she requires.\n\nGo through the application and do help us with your honest Ratings.\n\nWe have partnered with AppLovin Corporation to bring you a more social experience including but not limited to tools that allow you to: more easily invite your friends to your app, receive alerts from your friends, and receive social advertising. To serve you this experience we may share your personal data with AppLovin, and the use of your data by AppLovin is subject to AppLovin s Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. Both policies are available at www.applovin.com.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://apkpure.com/anatomy-guide-(pocket-book)/af.anatomy.guide/download?from=home', '2.2', 'https://lh3.ggpht.com/azpyZ9zcOtdn1UzgB3MA9grc0PJcSYHa2j0pOoiX-kTUNE03DMr-IwOJlI-jFn6wIQ=w72', 0, 4, 3061, 500, '2017-01-30 18:11:16', 'af.anatomy.guide', 0),
